<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10036k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10036k">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10036k"> 36(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> angarius (post) / corv&eacute;e</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans un de ses Capitulaires, Charlemagne ordonne: &ldquo;Que les <i>aldiones</i> (sujets affranchis sous condition de travail manuel), que les <i>libellarii</i> (affranchis par Acte public), de nouvelle ou d&apos;ancienne date, qui habitent une terre d&apos;Eglise, ne puissent &ecirc;tre forc&eacute;s ni contraints par le comte ni par un autre ministre, &agrave; servir aucune <i>angarie</i> (Postes), ni aucune autre corv&eacute;e publique ou priv&eacute;e.&rdquo; <font color="green">[In one of his capitulars, Charlemagne ordered &ldquo;That the aldiones (subjects freed on condition of manual labour), that the libellarii (freed by public act), of new or old commission, who inhabit land belonging to the Church cannot be forced or compelled by the count or by another minister to serve any angary (posts), or any other forced labour, whether public or private.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 44</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: French <i>Corv&eacute;e</i>, in feudal times a day&apos;s work of unpaid labour exacted by a lord from his vassal.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c01015b" href="c01all.htm#c01015b">VI.C.01:015(b)</a></mm></dd> </dd></dl>
